Basic description: Hinder the movement speed of up to four targets by 60 percent.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1631&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: A few wizards prefer to stick with the cheaper and faster Bonds of Force, but I notice the difference in results on Atol's, and use this as my snare spell. Keep an eye on the clock: This lasts two and a half minutes, so be prepared to reapply if something is about to come free. Note that this spell is also used as a turn-in for the Kunark wizard spell trade-in quests.<br>
Spell era: Ruins of Kunark<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: Sorcerer's Lexicon, Quill, Parchment, Rune of Conglomeration, Rune of Incendiary<br>
Quest information: This spell is not a quest reward in any known quests.<br>
Drop information: Various Kunark NPCs.<br>
<br>
Draught of Fire<br>
Basic description: This spell releases a rapid burst of fire, striking a single target.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1637&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Graffë's notes: Not as much damage as we are used to but wait until you see how fast you can roll off a multitude of these in a row. This is one of the most useful spells we have been given.<br>
Whizbang's notes: Here's where wizarding gets really interesting: Up until now, direct damage spells essentially just got bigger and more powerful as a wizard advanced in level. At first glance, the draught spells seem like a step backwards -- they don't hit as hard as Ice Comet or even Rend, and they certainly don't give the big impressive critical hits that wizards often look for. Look closer, though: Draughts cast as fast as some of our lowest level damage spells. In the time that you can cast one Ice Comet, you can cast two Draughts of Fire, which is two chances for a critical blast, and tying up just as much mana and casting time as you choose. If big blasts are a battle axe, the draughts are an extremely sharp dagger. Many wizards at this level and above greatly prefer draughts to big blasts, and I'm one of them.<br>
Spell era: Ruins of Kunark<br>
Vendor information: <br>
Firiona Vie, Selien Nartoise<br>
The Overthere, Tyrin F'Linz<br>
The Plane of Knowledge, Myrist, Channeler Olaemos<br>
Research information: This spell cannot be researched.<br>
Quest information: This spell is not a quest reward in any known quests.<br>
Drop information: This spell is not dropped by any known NPC.<br>
<br>
Levitation<br>
Basic description: Allows the target to bob in the air, defying most of the pull of gravity.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=2894&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: This is the bat wing-free upgrade to Levitate, and can only affect characters above level 45. An excellent spell, only made rare due to the fact that camping it is extremely tedious. (Trust me, I camped it.) Still, it sure beats carrying around a bunch of rotting old bat wings.<br>
Spell era: Shadows of Luclin<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: Sorcerer's Lexicon, Quill, Parchment, Rune of Conglomeration, Rune of Current<br>
Quest information: This spell is not a quest reward in any known quests.<br>
Drop information: The Deep, Deranged Underbulk<br>
<br>
Pillar of Frost<br>
Basic description: A targeted area of effect spell, ice based, that hits up to four targets.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1646&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: The long-awaited upgrade to our quad-kiting area of effect line. If wyverns ever go extinct, this spell will partially be to blame. Note that this spell is also used as a turn-in for the Kunark wizard spell trade-in quests.<br>
Spell era: Ruins of Kunark<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: Sorcerer's Lexicon, Quill, Parchment, Rune of Gale, Rune of Prexus<br>
Quest information: This spell is not a quest reward in any known quests.<br>
Drop information: Various Kunark NPCs.<br>
<br>
Tishan's Discord<br>
Basic description: <br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1634&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: A potent upgrade to our stun line.<br>
Spell era: Ruins of Kunark<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: Sorcerer's Lexicon, Quill, Parchment, Rune of Alternation, Rune of Vortex<br>
Quest information: <br>
Fironia Vie, Barnal Flamehand<br>
The Overthere, Utandar Rizndown<br>
